sentences: Read was born in Shanghai to an Estonian mother and English father in 1947.
She started her career at Vancouver Province in 1973 and her socially conscious column immediately became a must-read.
In 1985, her columns were collected into a book called Endless Summers and Other Shared Hallucinations.
She died of cancer at St. Paul's Hospital in Vancouver on December 21, 2007, aged 60, and was survived by her husband, playwright Michael Mercer, her father and a brother.
Jeani Read has died, Vancouver Jazz Society (2007-12-23).
The Province's Jeani Read dies of cancer, The Province (2007-12-23).
I dream of Jeani... a personal reminiscence, tributes, evalu8.org (2007-12-21).

sentences: Jeani Read (February 12, 1947 – December 21, 2007) was a Canadian journalist and columnist and a pioneer in rock music criticism in Canada.
In 1985, her columns were collected into a book called Endless Summers and Other Shared Hallucinations.
She was the first full-time rock critic at the Vancouver Province, a former lifestyles columnist and most recently, lifestyles reporter.
Endless summers and other shared hallucinations.
